<h1>Quickstart</h1>
<p class="lede">Sign up, copy your API key, create a one-off task with a webhook URL.</p>

<h2>1. Get an API key</h2>
<p><%= link_to "Sign up", signup_path %> or open <%= link_to "API Keys", docs_section_path("api-keys") %> if you already have an account.</p>

<h2>2. Connect your LLM provider</h2>
<p>
  Add your Anthropic or OpenAI key in <%= link_to "LLM Provider", docs_section_path("llm-provider") %>.
  Model usage is billed by your provider — Meerkat runs tasks using your key.
</p>

<h2>3. Create a one-off task</h2>
<pre><code>curl -X POST <%= api_base_url %>/tasks \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer mk_YOUR_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "task": {
      "task_type": "one_off",
      "description": "Fetch courier status and report findings",
      "input_params": {
        "courier_tracking_link": "https://..."
      },
      "output_webhook": "https://your-app.com/hook",
      "run_immediately": true
    }
  }'</code></pre>
<p><code>output_webhook</code> is required. <code>output_format</code> is optional and defaults to <code>default</code> — see <%= link_to "Webhooks", docs_section_path("webhooks") %>.</p>
<p>With <code>run_immediately: true</code> (default for one-off tasks), Meerkat runs the task right away and POSTs results to your webhook.</p>

<h2>4. Check the run</h2>
<pre><code>curl <%= api_base_url %>/tasks/1/runs \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer mk_YOUR_KEY"</code></pre>

<p><%= link_to "Task types →", docs_section_path("task-types") %> · <%= link_to "Full Tasks API →", docs_section_path("tasks") %></p>
